description:
&lt;p&gt;Nottinghamshire Low Secure and Community Forensic Directorate is a county wide specialist service, providing low secure treatment to adult male and female patients who have an identifiable mental illness, personality disorder or intellectual disability and a history of offending behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to recruit both Registered Mental Health Nurses and Registered Nurse Learning Disability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate is based at the Wells Road Centre in Nottingham and we have 5 established inpatient wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trent, Porchester and Thurland ward cater for male patients with a mental health diagnosis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The 4th male ward, Lister caters for those individuals with an Intellectual Disability Diagnosis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We also have one ward, Seacole which caters for 15 women with mental health issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service prides itself in providing an award-winning service. We were awarded 2nd place during the 2019 Peer review for delivering services within low secure standards developed by the Forensic Quality network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to deliver high quality, safe and effective care. Each patient receives a thorough assessment and implementation of comprehensive care packages. The care is aimed not only at treating the mental disorder but, addressing the offending or anti-social behaviours. The Directorate is committed to providing a service where the individuality of each patient is respected, regardless of ethnic origin, age, gender, background, religion, sexual orientation or personal beliefs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be committed to being part of a modern and professional nursing team within a multi disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Staff Nurse you will promote and maintain high standards of care through communication, motivation, supervision and role modelling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are newly qualified, we will support you through your preceptor-ship offering valuable support and guidance to provide you with the skills to be a competent, caring and safe practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is an opportunity to develop valuable forensic experience and share excellent practice in a setting that’s uniquely demanding and exceptionally rewarding. The wards at the Wells Road Centre offer exciting opportunities for personal and professional development through education and training, clinical supervision and staff appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will be committed to provide you with training, team support, supervision and opportunities for personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We understand that you will want to develop your own unique skills and competences which we will help you to achieve. We provide a comprehensive training package at the start of your employment with us ranging from prevention and management of aggression, risk assessment, substance misuse, self harm, observation and engagement of patients and you will be supported to complete an induction package&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to work a 7 day roster, 24-hour shift pattern, including night shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our DBS check is free, you have no fees to pay!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For nursing roles graduating in 2020/21; and gaining employment in the same financial year; the first year of professional member fees will be paid as incentive to employment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
